  "texts": [
    "Octoparse is a free web scraping software that takes unstructured data and text from websites and exports them to a structured data file.",
    "This focused approach ensured that the corpus consisted solely of questions directly relevant to the topic, thereby strengthening the meaningfulness and relevance of the data collected.",
    "By concentrating on questions that explicitly mentioned deepfakes, we aimed to capture answers covering a comprehensive range of perspectives and discussions surrounding this emerging technology.",
    "This methodological choice was essential in ensuring that the subsequent analysis accurately reflected public opinions and mental representations of deepfake.",
    "The final text corpus consisted of 166 answers to 17 questions."
